## Testing Lifecycle Hooks

```ts
it("cleans up event listeners on unmount", () => {
  const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, "addEventListener");
  const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(window, "removeEventListener");

  const { wrapper } = mountComposable(() => useWindowSize());
  expect(addSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith("resize", expect.any(Function));

  wrapper.unmount();
  expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith("resize", expect.any(Function));
});
```

## Conventions

- Use `withSetup` helper for simple composables
- Use `mountComposable` when lifecycle or DOM is needed
- `setActivePinia` in `beforeEach` for Pinia tests
- Test reactive values via `.value`
- Verify lifecycle cleanup by unmounting wrapper
